d with a small smile, the orange sunset now low on the horizon and casting long reflections on the water.) (At 3 seconds: The wave loses energy; he steps back gently on the board to slow his speed, riding it more upright.) (At 4 seconds: He pumps the board lightly to keep gliding, the waning wave still carrying him toward the shore.) (At 5 seconds: He raises one hand briefly in a small celebratory gesture, the silhouette catching the deep amber sky behind him.)\n\n(At 0 seconds: The wave has fully tapered; the same surfer drops back into a prone position on the longboard as the water flattens.) (At 1 seconds: He paddles a few easy strokes toward the shore, the warm sunset reflecting off the gentle ripples around him.) (At 2 seconds: He rolls the board sideways, slipping into the water with practiced grace, the longboard floating beside him.) (At 3 seconds: He grips the rail of the board and turns it back toward the open ocean, eyes scanning for the next swell.) (At 4 seconds: He climbs back onto the board with a single fluid motion and resumes a relaxed paddling rhythm.) (At 5 seconds: He glides back out into the orange-gold horizon, silhouette small against the wide, calm ocean.)"
